The emphasis on land and natural resources management has not been a new development in contemporary Uganda. It emanates from legitimate uses of the land and natural resources under traditional laws which have been left over when King Mutesa ascended to the throne and his rule rehabilitated some

The main export crops are coffee, cotton, tobacco, tea and sugar. Livestock sector also plays a huge role in Uganda's economy. About 60 percent of the cultivated area is conserved as land for grazing purposes (as compared to 7 percent in Kenya and 20 percent in Tanzania). Small Pigs, chicken and goats are raised frequently by the majority of the smallholder farmers.
